The paper focuses on comparing and evaluating two popular methods for image instance retrieval - Convolutional Neural Nets (CNNs) and Fisher Vectors (FVs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of geometrical transformations on the performance of these methods, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
